1975  || Track formation around the island platform remains \n|-\n| [[Newnes Junction railway station|Newnes Junction (#2)]]{{efn|Stations from [[Newnes Junction railway station|Newnes Junction]] to [[Lithgow Zig Zag|Bottom Points]] of the [[Lithgow Zig Zag|Great Lithgow Zig Zag]] were closed on 16 October 1910 with the opening of the [[Ten Tunnels Deviation]] also referred to as the 1910 Deviation. The Zig Zag was bypassed due to increased rail traffic across the Blue Mountains. The Ten Tunnels Deviation was constructed as double track to handle the increased traffic. Today, the ten tunnels are electrified and also signalled to run trains in both directions on both tracks. Bi-Directional running.}} || 16 October 1910  || 6 April 1975  || The station has a signal box on it for Clarence Colliery coal train movements\n|-\n| [[Newnes Junction railway station|Newnes Junction (#1)]] || 27 November 1906 || 16 October 1910 || \n|-\n| [[Clarence railway stations|Clarence (#1)]] || 1874 || 16 October 1910 || \n|-\n| [[Lithgow Zig Zag|Top Points]] ||  ||  || \n|-\n| [[Lithgow Zig Zag|Bottom Points]] ||  ||  || \n|-\n| [[Zig Zag Railway|Clarence (#2)]] || 16 October 1910 || 21 September 1974 || 1910 Deviation\n|-\n| [[Lithgow railway station|Eskbank (formerly Lithgow)]]  || June 1874 ||  || \n|-\n| [[Cooerwull railway station|Cooerwull]] ||  ||  || \n|-\n| [[Bowenfels railway station|Bowenfels]] ||  18 October 1869 ||  21 September 1974 || \n|-\n| rowspan=2| North Sydney Car Sidings || Milsons Point (#2) ||   ||   || \n|-\n| Milsons Point (#1) ||   ||   || \n|-\n| rowspan=9| [[Richmond railway line|Richmond]] || Mulgrave Tank Platform ||   ||   || \n|-\n| Phillip Platform ||   || 26 July 1952 ||\n|-\n| North Richmond || 8 December 1926 || 26 July 1952 ||\n|-\n| Red Cutting Halt || September 1928 || 26 July 1952 ||\n|-\n| Kemsleys Platform || September 1928 || 26 July 1952 ||\n|-\n| Thompsons Ridge || November 1928 || 26 July 1952 || Platform closed\n|-\n| Nurri Halt || September 1928 || 26 July 1952 ||\n|-\n| Duffys Halt || September 1928 || 26 July 1952 ||\n|-\n| Kurrajong  || 8 December 1926 || 26 July 1952 ||\n|-\n| rowspan=11 | [[Rogans Hill railway line|Rogans Hill]] || Mons Road Platform || 28 January 1923 || 31 January 1932 || \n|-\n| Northmead Platform || 28 January 1923 || 1 January 1932 || \n|-\n| Moxhams Road Platform || 28 January 1923 || 1 February 1932 ||\n|-\n| Model Farms Road Platform || 28 January 1923 || 1 February 1932 ||\n|-\n| Junction Road Platform || 28 January 1923 || 1 February 1932 ||\n|-\n| Baulkham Hills Platform || 28 January 1923 || 1 February 1932 ||\n|-\n| Cross Street Platform || 28 January 1923 || 1 February 1932 ||\n|-\n| Southleigh Platform || 28 January 1923 || 1 February 1932 ||\n|-\n| Parsonage Lane Platform || December 1923 || 1 February 1932 ||\n|-\n| Castle Hill Platform || 28 January 1923 || 1 February 1932 ||\n|-\n| Rogans Hill Platform || 24 November 1924 || 1 February 1932 ||\n|-\n| rowspan=4| [[Rookwood Cemetery railway line|Rookwood Cemetery]] || [[Cemetery Station No. 1 railway station|Cemetery No. 1]] ||   ||   || <ref name=\"station_names\">State Rail Authority of New South Wales Archives Section, ''How & Why of Station Names: meanings and origins...'', Second Edition, 1982, State Rail Authority of New South Wales,</ref>\n|-\n| [[Cemetery Station No. 2 railway station|Cemetery No. 2]] ||   ||   || <ref name=\"station_names\" />\n|-\n| [[Cemetery Station No. 3 railway station|Cemetery No. 3]] ||   ||   || <ref name=\"station_names\" />\n|-\n| [[Cemetery Station No. 4 railway station|Cemetery No. 4]] ||   ||   || <ref name=\"station_names\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=3| [[Ropes Creek railway line|Ropes Creek]] || [[Dunheved railway station|Dunheved]] || 1 March 1942 || 22 March 1986 ||\n|-\n| [[Cochrane railway station, Sydney|Cochrane]] || 2 September 1957 || 22 March 1986 ||\n|-\n| [[Ropes Creek railway station|Ropes Creek]] || 29 June 1942 || 22 March 1986 || \n|-\n| rowspan=4| [[Sandown railwa